dct_description_sm: United States. Geological Survey. U.S.G.S. Alternate title: Bordentown. Relief shown by 10 feet contour interval. Surveyed in 1885. Triangulation by the U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey. Revised in 1904. Map shows Camp Dix and rifle range. (Camp Dix was later renamed Fort Dix and as of 2005 will be Joint Base Maguire-Dix-Lakehurst.) Verso: legend and explanatory notes, "The topographic maps of the United States".
